Is Europe’s elite ready to do business with the UK?
Business for Britain was launched in April with the intention of bringing the economy to a table and defining what those in the UK who care about prosperity and jobs want to change in our relationship with the EU.
To this end, we commissioned the largest and most comprehensive survey among UK economic leaders and asked them what they think about the UK, the economy and the EU.
YouGov surveyed more than 1,000 business leaders, representing roughly the UK’s corporate sizes, sectors and regions.
The results of the survey will surprise many.
We have found that the vast majority of companies are now exporting outside of Europe, focusing on countries that are modernising and growing while countries in the EU are stagnating.
They want new trade links with countries such as China, India and Brazil to be favoured by the government, rather than stopping with the long and grueling process of reforming the obscure EU institutions.
